                <h1 class="appHeaderName">BlueDeck</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12">
                <p>
                    BlueDeck was designed to help manage personnel rosters and organizational structure in an
                    environment where relationships change frequently. Development of this software is ongoing, so you
                    may experience errors or other strange behavior. Please report any issues to the administrator at
                    <a href="mailto:admin@BlueDeck.net">Admin@BlueDeck.net</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        @{
            if (MemberId == "0")
            {
                <p>
                    <a class="btn btn-default" style="color:white" asp-action="Register" asp-controller="Home">Get an Account</a>
                </p>
            }
            else
            {
                <p>
                    <a class="btn btn-default" style="color:white" asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Home">Go to my Homepage</a>
                </p>
            }
        }
    </div>
</div>
<div class="aboutPageContent">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <div class="aboutPageContentContainer">
                <img src="~/lib/bluedeck/css/images/OrgChartIcon.png" class="pull-left" height="100" width="100" />
                <h3>Organization Charts</h3>
                <p>
                    You can use BlueDeck to <a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="OrgChart">View, search, </a> or <a href="#">Export</a> organization charts for Components, Positions, and Members.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <div class="aboutPageContentContainer">
                <img src="~/lib/bluedeck/css/images/Roster.png" class="pull-left" height="100" width="100" />
                <h3>Personnel Rosters</h3>
                <p>
                    You can use BlueDeck's <a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Roster">Roster Manager</a> to assign/transfer employees and track unit demographics.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
            <div class="aboutPageContentContainer">
                <img src="~/lib/bluedeck/css/images/search-512.png" class="pull-left" height="100" width="100" />
                <h3>Find People</h3>
                <p>
                    BlueDeck can help you find <a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Members">Member information</a> such as email addresses, contact numbers, and assignments.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


